<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="131" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-11"><hi rend="italic">June 11,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Prince Tuan, father Heir-Apparent, has been appointed president of the
                            Tsungli Yamen, with three other new ministers, all greatly opposed to
                            foreigners. Situation not improved. Seven hundred additional guards
                            repairing railway en route. Their arrival will assure safety foreigners
                            here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>